# sync-pairs.txt
#
# List the folders you want to sync to your NAS, one per line.
#
# Format:
#   /source/path:/destination/path
#
#   - Source path: the path INSIDE the container (map your host folder to this
#     via a volume mount in docker-compose.yml or your docker run command)
#   - Destination path: the path on the NAS (must already exist)
#   - Separator: a single colon (:)
#
# Rules:
#   - Blank lines are ignored
#   - Lines starting with # are comments
#   - Each pair must have exactly one colon separating source and destination
#
# What happens during sync:
#   - Files are copied to the NAS over SSH using rsync
#   - Source files are DELETED after a successful transfer
#   - Empty directories are cleaned up after the transfer
#   - If a transfer fails, the source files are left in place
#
# Examples:

# /data/photos:/volume1/backups/photos
# /data/documents:/volume1/backups/documents
# /data/downloads:/volume1/media/incoming
